      <mn>4</mn>
    </mrow>
  </msub>
</mrow><annotation encoding="math/tex">\text{H}_{2}\text{SO}_{4}</annotation></semantics></math></p></li><li><p>Name and write the formula of some common strong bases (group 1 hydroxides) and weak bases (ammonia solution and carbonates).</p></li><li><p>Write the reaction equations, with double arrows to show reversibility, for ionisation of any known or given acids dissolving in water.</p></li><li><p>Write the reaction equations, with double arrows to show reversibility, for dissociation of any known or given bases dissolving in water.</p></li><li><p>Define a strong acid as <em>an acid that ionises almost completely in an aqueous solution</em>.</p></li><li></li></ul></div></body>
